      <title>Newly discovered planet is more than 600 light years away from Earth.</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANA team of scientists in India have discovered a sub-Saturn sized exoplanet, reports the Financial Times.The planet, called EPIC 211945201b or K2-236b, is reportedly 600 light years away from Earth.The planet has a mass of around 27 Earths while its radius is six times that of Earth. Scientists used the PRL Advance Radial-velocity Abu-sky Search spectrograph, or PARAS, to measure the mass of a planet travelling around a star.The surface temperature of the planet is approximately 600 degrees Celsius, which makes it virtually uninhabitable. Distance-wise, it is seven times closer to its sun-like star in comparison to Earth and its sun.It takes around 19.5 days to complete one rotation around its Sun-like star.The scientists believe elements such as ice, silicates, and iron content make up around 60-70 percent of the total mass of the planet, based on the calculations of the mass and the radius, reports The Economic Times.This type of a discovery is crucial in our understanding of how these types of planets are formed, the Financial Express reports. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Showing the new planet and how far away it is from Earth2. Showing how big the new planet is compared to Earth.3. Showing the surface of K2-236b and we also see how close the planet is to its Sun-like Star4. Showing how  K2-236b rotates around its Sun-like Star and we also see the elements that may makeup K2-236b. VOICEOVER (in English): "The planet's sun-like star is reportedly 600 light years away from Earth.""The planet has a mass of around 27 Earths while its radius is six times that of Earth. ""The surface temperature of the planet is approximately 600 degrees Celsius, which makes it virtually uninhabitable. Distance-wise, it is seven times closer to its sun-like star in comparison to Earth and its sun.""It takes around 19.5 days to complete one rotation around its Sun-like star.""The Economic Times reports that the scientists believe elements such as ice, silicates, and iron content make up around 60-70 percent of the total mass of the planet, based on the calculations of the mass and the radius."SOURCES: The Economic Times, Financial Express, The Times of India,https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/science/indian-scientists-discover-planet-600-light-years-away/light-years-away-from-earth/slideshow/64509281.cmshttps://www.financialexpress.com/lifestyle/science/india-discovers-its-own-planet-where-a-year-ends-in-19-5-days-amazing-things-to-know/1200647/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/science/india-discovers-new-planet-joins-elite-club/articleshow/64515199.cms***]]></description>
