      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANFive people are dead and many others injured after a man with targeted a newspaper office in Maryland.The Baltimore Sun reports that a suspect wielding a shotgun and smoke grenades shot through the glass doors of the Capital Gazette office around 2:40 p.m. on Thursday.According to one witness, he opened fire on several people, killing two women and three men, and injuring at least three others.Employees reportedly hid under their desks during the deadly incident and pleaded for help on social media.Police arrived within a minute of the shooting, surrounding the gunman and taking him into custody. Civilians were escorted out of the building soon after.The shooter was later identified as 38-year-old Jarrod Ramos, a local with a long-standing grudge against the Capital Gazette. He previously sued the paper for defamation, but lost after failing to prove that what the paper published about him was RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Depiction of gunman shooting glass office doors2. Depiction of shooter gunning down newspaper employees3. Depiction of employees hiding under desks4. Depiction of police apprehending suspectVOICEOVER (in English): "A suspect wielding a shotgun and smoke grenades shot through the glass doors of the Capital Gazette office around 2:40 p.m. on Thursday.""According to one witness, he opened fire on several people, killing two women and three men, and injuring at least three others.""Employees reportedly hid under their desks during the deadly incident and asked for help over social media.""Police arrived within a minute of the shooting, surrounding the gunman and taking him into custody. Civilians were escorted out of the building soon after."SOURCES: Baltimore